title: What is the trend for asthma, diabetes and epilepsy unplanned emergency admissions for the under 19s?
analysis_commentary: The rate of emergency admissions for asthma, diabetes and epilepsy in children and young people has declined from 345.9 per 100,000 in 2003/04 to 313.4 per 100,000 in 2013/14; a decrease of 9.4%.
data_source: NHS Outcomes Framework, Health and Social Care Information Centre
